##################################
#  Initialization

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

#######################################
#  Setup

TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("Numeric");

$r = non_zero_random(-8,8,2);
$s = random(-5,4,2);
$prod = 2*$r*$s;
$sum = 2*($r+$s);
$fact_prod = $r*$s;
$fact_sum = $r+$s;
$neg_r = -$r;
$neg_s = -$s;

$answer = List(Real("$neg_r"),Real("$neg_s"));

#  tex strings
$x = "r";
$f = "Q(r)";
$func = "2 r^2 + $sum r + $prod";


###########################################
#  Main text

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Find the zeros of \( $f = $func. \)
If more than one zero exists,
enter your answers as a comma separated list.
If no zeroes exist, enter ${BBOLD}NONE${EBOLD}.
$PAR
The zeros are \( $x = \)
\{ ans_rule(20) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("number") \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;


########################################
#  Answer evaluation

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

ANS($answer->cmp() );


########################################
#  Solution

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
In order to find the zeros, we set the function equal to zero and solve for \(r\) by factoring:
\[\begin{aligned}
 2 r^2 + $sum r + $prod  &= 0\\
 2 \left( r^2 + $fact_sum r + $fact_prod \right) &= 0 \\
 2 ( r + $r)(r + $s) &= 0
\end{aligned}\]
$PAR
Since \( (r + $r ) \) and \( (r + $s ) \) are factors, there are two zeros at \( r = $neg_r \) and \( r = $neg_s \).

END_SOLUTION


;
